/Force                     Reapplies all policy settings. By default,\r\n

/Wait:{value}              Sets the number of seconds to wait for policy\r\n
processing to finish. The default is 600\r\n

When the time limit is exceeded, the command\r\n

/Logoff                    Causes a logoff after the Group Policy settings\r\n
have been refreshed. This is required for\r\n
those Group Policy client-side extensions\r\n
that do not process policy on a background\r\n
refresh cycle but do process policy when a\r\n
user logs on. Examples include user-targeted\r\n
Software Installation and Folder Redirection.\r\n
This option has no effect if there are no\r\n
extensions called that require a logoff.\r\n\r\n
/Boot                      Causes a reboot after the Group Policy settings\r\n
are refreshed. This is required for those\r\n
Group Policy client-side extensions that do\r\n
not process policy on a background refresh cycle\r\n
but do process policy at computer startup.\r\n

Installation. This option has no effect if\r\n
there are no extensions called that require\r\n
a reboot.\r\n\r\n
/Sync                      Causes the next foreground policy application to\r\n
be done synchronously. Foreground policy\r\n
applications occur at computer boot and user\r\n
logon. You can specify this for the user,\r\n
computer or both using the /Target parameter.\r\n

if specified.\r\n\r\n
